systemd is a system and service manager for Linux
==================================================
systemctl - List running units
systemctl list-units - List running units
systemctl --failed - List failled units
systemctl list-unit-files - List unit files

systemctl reload unit - Reload a unit
systemctl is-enabled unit - Check availability
systemctl help unit - Check manual page with a unit
systemctl daemon-reload - Reload systemd, scanning for new or changed units:

systemctl reboot
systemctl poweroff
systemctl suspend
systemctl hibernate
systemctl hybrid-sleep

systemctl --state=failed - failed services

systemctl --type=service --> To find currently running services

